  • Classes in com.microsoft.azure.management.compute used by com.microsoft.azure.management.compute 
    Class and Description
    AvailabilitySet
    An immutable client-side representation of an Azure availability set.
    AvailabilitySet.DefinitionBlank
    The first stage of an availability set definition
    AvailabilitySet.DefinitionCreatable
    The stage of an availability set definition which contains all the minimum required inputs for the resource to be created (via Creatable.create()), but also allows for any other optional settings to be specified.
    AvailabilitySet.DefinitionWithGroup
    The stage of the availability set definition allowing to specify the resource group
    DataDisk
    A data disk of a virtual machine.
    DataDisk.DefinitionAttachable
    The stage of the data disk definition which contains all the minimum required inputs for the resource to be attached (via DataDisk.DefinitionAttachable.attach()), but also allows for any other optional settings to be specified.
    DataDisk.DefinitionAttachExistingDataDisk
    The first stage of attaching an existing disk as data disk and configuring it.
    DataDisk.DefinitionAttachNewDataDisk
    The first stage of new data disk configuration.
    DataDisk.DefinitionWithOptionalConfiguration
    The stage of the data disk configuration allowing to specify optionals common for new and attachable existing data disks.
    DataDisk.DefinitionWithStoreAt
    The stage of the data disk configuration allowing to specify location to store the VHD.
    VirtualMachine
    An immutable client-side representation of an Azure virtual machine.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionCreatable
    The stage of the virtual machine definition which contains all the minimum required inputs for the resource to be created (via Creatable.create()), but also allows for any other optional settings to be specified.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionLinuxCreatable
    The stage of the Linux virtual machine definition which contains all the minimum required inputs for the resource to be created (via Creatable.create()), but also allows for any other optional settings to be specified.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionOSDiskSettings
    The stage of the virtual machine definition allowing to specify OS disk configurations.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionPassword
    The stage of the virtual machine definition allowing to specify password.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionStorageAccount
    The stage of the virtual machine definition allowing to specify storage account.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionWindowsCreatable
    The stage of the Windows virtual machine definition which contains all the minimum required inputs for the resource to be created (via Creatable.create()), but also allows for any other optional settings to be specified.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionWithAdminUserName
    The stage of the Windows virtual machine definition allowing to specify administrator user name.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionWithAvailabilitySet
    The stage of the virtual machine definition allowing to specify availability set.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionWithDataDisk
    The stage of the virtual machine definition allowing to specify data disk configuration.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionWithMarketplaceImage
    The stage of the virtual machine definition allowing to specify marketplace (platform) image.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionWithOS
    The stage of the virtual machine definition allowing to specify the Operation System.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionWithOSType
    The stage of the virtual machine definition allowing to specify Operating system type.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionWithRootUserName
    The stage of the Linux virtual machine definition allowing to specify root user name.
    VirtualMachine.DefinitionWithVMSize
    The stage of the virtual machine definition allowing to specify VM size.
    VirtualMachineImage
    An immutable client-side representation of an Azure virtual machine image.
    VirtualMachineImage.Offer
    Represents a virtual machine image offer.
    VirtualMachineImage.Publisher
    Represents a virtual image image publisher.
    VirtualMachineImage.Sku
    Represents a virtual machine image SKU.
    VirtualMachineSize
    A type representing virtual machine size available for a subscription in a region.
